HEADWORD: Sassy bark
<hw>Sas"sy bark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The bark of a
West African leguminous tree (<spn>Erythrophlaeum Guineense</spn>, used
by the natives as an ordeal poison, and also medicinally; -- called also
<altname>mancona bark</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

